.TH MDNS\-BROWSE 1 "2026-04-15" "truenas-pydiscovery" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mdns\-browse \- browse for mDNS/DNS\-SD services
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mdns\-browse
.RB [ \-a ]
.RB [ \-r ]
.RB [ \-t
.IR TIMEOUT ]
.RB [ \-i
.IR ADDR ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.RI [ SERVICE_TYPE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mdns\-browse
sends mDNS queries directly on the network to discover services.
It runs continuously, printing newly discovered services as they appear,
until interrupted with Ctrl\-C or the timeout expires.
.PP
No daemon is required.
Queries use the QU (unicast\-response) bit on an ephemeral port.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I SERVICE_TYPE
Service type to browse (e.g.\ \fB_http._tcp\fP).
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Browse for all service types via the
.I _services._dns\-sd._udp
meta\-query.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-resolve
Auto\-resolve each discovered service to show hostname, port,
addresses, and TXT records.
.TP
.BI \-t " TIMEOUT" "\fR,\fP \-\-timeout " TIMEOUT
Total browse duration in seconds.
Default: run until Ctrl\-C.
.TP
.BI \-i " ADDR" "\fR,\fP \-\-interface " ADDR
Interface IPv4 address to send queries from.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output as JSONL (one JSON object per line per discovered service).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
mdns\-browse _http._tcp
mdns\-browse \-\-all \-\-resolve
mdns\-browse _smb._tcp \-\-json \-t 10
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mdns\-resolve (1),
.BR mdns\-lookup (1),
.BR truenas\-mdnsd (8)
